Makers Club: April
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
Makers Club meets the first Tuesday of every month at 8:00pm. https://www.facebook.com/groups/makersclubsf/ Makers Club is for anyone who makes things professionally. Designers, artists, architects, photographers, illustrators, typographers, filmmakers, writers, programmers, printers, copywriters, carpenters, etcetera are all welcome. There is no agenda, it's not for recruiting, the point is just to meet, talk, and drink with other interesting people. Simple. "Good things happen when nice people get drunk together." —Nicholas Arioli

An Evening with Juliet Macur
Mark Zuckerberg was invited
Scribd invites you to an intimate discussion with Juliet Macur, New York Times journalist and author of Cycle of Lies: The Fall of Lance Armstrong. Hosted at one of San Francisco's most historic and elegant spaces, The Box SF, the event will feature an exclusive discussion and Q&A with Juliet, meet-and-greet and book signing. Beer, wine and appetizers will also be provided. If you're a Scribd reader you'll receive a free copy of Cycle of Lies: The Fall of Lance Armstrong (supplies are limited - first come first serve). If you're not a Scribd member, you're more than welcome to sign up for a special 3-month trial now using the promo code: CycleOfLies. http://www.scribd.com/promo_code/CycleOfLies Space is limited so please RSVP here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/an-evening-with-juliet-macur-tickets-11963510181
